social_posts.post_text: First post of the year. January 4, 2023. The Pacific Ocean on a rainy day in Los Angeles. Hope everyone has a great year ahead. May the rain and calm be symbolic for a year of peace for all. It's a crazy world out there so that won't be easy. But hoping for it...

Throwback to the year I moved to LA after graduating from the University of Virginia (a few years back....) reading the Hollywood Reporter looking for what movies were being cast so I could send a headshot to the casting offices #tbt
Thank you all for the birthday wishes today. Means a lot to me.
Cause it's Wednesday night

If you know me you know how passionate I am about this project. It took two different owners 18 years to get it approved by the city of Malibu and current ownership and my team have spent a lot of time working on leasing it the last 3 years from dirt to how it looks today. It's set to open later this year. Marmol- Radziner @marmolradziner has designed the project. We will be announcing some of the best brands in the country/ world soon but we aren't fully leased yet. I am posting this to remind my friends who either are the brands, who rep the brands or who dm me with ideas all the time that this is going to be one of the most special developments in the country. If you want to know who we have signed I can tell you, but I can't post publicly yet. We have coffee, ice cream, bars, restaurants, fitness tenants and really cool retailers. Some known coast to coast doing their first stores here. We also have tons of parking. Over 500 spaces and some of the coolest office buildings that exist (last two pics). For a marketing flyer please ask me for it or go to jayluchs.com, featured properties, Malibu, for lease. It's called Cross Creek Ranch Malibu. I'll be posting current pics on my stories again after the rain stops and we see sun again. These pics were taken a month ago. We want to make this the best new project in the country and it likely will be. Located near the country mart on Civic Center Drive steps from Cross Creek Road. And the best part is that while the design and tenant mix is second to none, the back drop are the mountains. You can't create those! It's very special.....

KITH opened its doors today on Rodeo Drive. First pic was taken in 2018 when fashion and footwear designer Ronnie Fieg and I were looking for locations on the street. Never an easy task per lack of spaces available, Ronnie told me I couldn't post it until we opened a store on Rodeo Drive. I soon found him a location, but from beginning to end with ups and downs it took almost 5 years to open and last night he and the KITH team had a celebration at the store and dinner after at newly opened Caviar Kaspia (on Melrose Place). I'm extra proud of this deal and in shock at what he and the KITH team do. It's not normal. It's from another planet from the merch to collabs to the build out to the experience. KITH Treats is also now open in the store for anyone else who craves great ice cream and don't forget the cereal bar. From street to luxury KITH has created something special. Thanks to the others involved who helped get this deal done. Pros for sure who I respect and admire. I wish them much success at 262 N Rodeo Drive. I proudly post this pic today that Ronnie wouldn't let me that day. We did it. Congratulations @ronniefieg @dotcash @kith @kithfootwear

Every year there is an annual shopping center/ retail convention for commercial real estate owners, tenants and brokers in Las Vegas. There are two or three days of back to back meetings in the convention center and other meetings and dinners with people from across the country and world we don't always get to stay in touch with. It was great to see everyone these last few days. 

Also, I haven't done a market update video in a year and will do one soon as there is a lot to talk about. The world is in a weird place from high interest rates to people not wanting to go back into offices, but there is some good in it all too. I'm happy to say retailers and restaurants are active thanks to consumers wanting to get out and enjoy their lives as much as they can post covid. More to follow for those who have interest in hearing......

May 26, 2023. This is not an update on the economy and commericial real estate. Just my thoughts about the LVMH owned Cheval Blanc being turned down by the voters of Beverly Hills yesterday. I don't see how it would have hurt anyone and am confident it would have enhanced an area. As good as places can be they do get stale and the Peter Marino designed spectacular hotel project on Santa Monica Blvd between Rodeo Drive and Beverly Drive would have been a gift to the city adding jobs, tax revenue and beauty. That part of the block has always been the end zone and hardest to lease and could have become a gem in the city. It's embarrassing and unfortunate. Life goes on and what's meant to be will be, but this is one I don't get. This isn't a small town in the middle of the country. This should be a city welcoming international tourists and local traffic offering more options to the community. All this does is suck the energy out. Each vote adds up. Margin was slim. This doesn't send a good message to the retail, food and beverage, hospitality, tourist and local community. It sets us back in time.

I'm sad to say that we lost my dad this weekend from Parkinson's disease. He was the greatest father I could ever ask for. He loved my mom, sister and me and his grandchildren Harrison and Logan so much. I'll always remember the special times together from vacations to going to football games together and all of his kind, positive energy. He also supported my moving to Los Angeles after college which I'm sure isn't an easy thing to do as a parent. My friends all loved being around him and he loved them back. He accomplished so much in his 85 years. He lived a long life but the last few years have been extremely tough and he is out of his pain now. Celebrating my incredible dad Kenneth J Luchs. In my heart forever ❤️

Thank you @labusinessjournal / writer Brynn Shaffer for writing this article. Didn't realize asking me some questions about my career and what's going on out there would turn into this. Thank you. It captured my love for Los Angeles, my early love for the entertainment business which I spent time in, real estate and how it got going for me, my love for my family history back east and the culture of Los Angeles, my admiration for vintage things to the current brands and clients I represent and the fun I am having with a California inspired casual clothing line not just the "for lease" sign merch, but with the up and coming brand "California Incline" with @kelseychapman_ selling California culture merchandise including hoodies, hats, t's and crew necks supporting the beaches up and down the coast focusing on Malibu surf points. There will also be a store opening at Cross Creek Ranch Malibu late in 2024 selling the merch, cool books and photography taken on the California coast for both locals and tourists to be proud to wear around. Also talked about is my residential business with @steven_schaefer for the purchase and sale of homes all over LA from Beverly Hills to Brentwood to the Pacific Palisades and Malibu. My day job and passion is the sale and leasing of commercial real estate focussing on finding locations for retailers, fashions brands, restaurants etc... I am lucky for my team who work hard to help make this what it is (Inee Byun, Genny Chang, Carly Geller, Gavin Ketchum, James Nugent, Corinne Wang and Britney Kagawa). Thanks LABJ for having some fun with me. It's a ton of hard work, but also something I enjoy and get so caught up that I forget it's work #losangeles #california

This was in my stories early last week but have to let it live on the main page... thanks @therealdeal and reporter @andrewaschofficial for your interest in doing this story on what a work day is like for me. I want to dedicate time next year to talking to kids about their careers. I feel like many are lost in the glamour, but the quickest way to build a real career is put in some hard hours in the early years when others are trying to skip through it. Build knowledge, soul and a heart and no one will stop you. Happy holidays. Much love ❤️
